<LayoutWithClampedFooter title="Blog • Catppuccin" description="News and Stories about Catppuccin">
  <PageIntro title="Blog">
    <p>Catppuccin News and whatever. ¯\_(ツ)_/¯</p>
  </PageIntro>

  <section class="bloglist">
    <ArticleCard author="Hammy" pubDate={new Date("2024-11-22")}>
      <h3 slot="article-title">The Science of Color: How to Choose the Perfect Palette for Your Project</h3>
      <p slot="article-content">
        Choosing the right color palette for your project isn’t just about aesthetics—there’s real science behind it.
        From color theory and the psychology of hues to the impact of light and contrast, understanding the principles
        of color can help you make more informed design choices. In this post, we’ll explore how to select colors based
        on your project’s goals, whether you’re designing for visual impact, readability, or emotional engagement. With
        practical tips and color formulas, you'll learn how to create a palette that works as hard as your design does.
      </p>
    </ArticleCard>
    <ArticleCard author="Pepperchonk" pubDate={new Date("2024-11-02")} category="community">
      <h3 slot="article-title">5 Common Mistakes to Avoid When Building a Color Scheme (And How to Fix Them)</h3>
      <p slot="article-content">
        Developing a successful color scheme isn’t just about choosing your favorite colors—it’s about making
        intentional choices that create balance, contrast, and visual appeal. In this post, we’ll cover five common
        mistakes designers and creators make when selecting colors, from overusing bright hues to ignoring accessibility
        needs. We’ll also offer practical tips to avoid these pitfalls and help you craft a color palette that’s both
        stunning and functional.
      </p>
    </ArticleCard>
    <ArticleCard author="Pocco" pubDate={new Date("2024-10-18")} category="announcement">
      <h3 slot="article-title">Mastering the Art of Color Schemes</h3>
      <p slot="article-content">
        When designing for any project—whether it’s a website, brand identity, or interior design—the color scheme is
        often the first thing that grabs attention. But how do you pick the right palette? In this guide, we'll walk you
        through the fundamentals of color theory and how to combine colors that not only look great together but also
        evoke the right emotional response. From primary and secondary colors to the psychology behind each hue, we’ll
        help you develop a cohesive scheme that resonates with your audience.
      </p>
    </ArticleCard>
  </section>
</LayoutWithClampedFooter>

